04/08/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- General George Antonakopoulos, chief of the national defence general staff, said Tuesday (3 August) that the armed forces are fully prepared to handle any security issues during the Athens Olympics.
He said a total of 234 aircraft and helicopters, 51 Greek Navy vessels and 28 anti-aircraft missile batteries will be included in a security network created by the armed forces for the Games.
Defence units will be on constant alert to confront any possible terrorist attack, he added.
(ANA - 03/08/04)
